   "content": [
      {
         "id": "SECTION_prerequisites",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "<p><span id=\"htZoomImageMsg\"></span></p><p><span id=\"htAmericaAbyaYalaMsg\"></span> (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('160fb48c-1711-491e-a1aa-e1257e7889af'); return false;\">Porto-Gonçalves, Carlos Walter, <htdate0>, pp. 39-43</a>).</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": [
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2011",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  }
               ],
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><h3>Prerequisites</h3>The game on this page aims to reinforce knowledge of indigenous numerical systems and the numbers we use today. Before starting, we suggest studying the following previous pages:</p><p><ul><li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('20b14681-88c0-438a-a273-a0902ae5db38'); return false;\">Our sides are equal</a>: in this first text, we show for people their body symmetry.</li> <li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('3874d1e8-0f76-4432-9ee2-d8c8c9dccf53'); return false;\">Couting</a>: we introduce the idea of counting using our body.</li> <li><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('cc8c1467-a6af-4f9c-ba60-ab6df35aba05'); return false;\">Beyond fingers</a>: exploring the limitations and the necessity of new tools to count.</li></ul></p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_trainee",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "<p><h3>Training steps</h3><b>Objective:</b>There is a relationship between our fingers and the symbols we use to count. In this step as a trainee, your mission is to complete the counting sequence using different models. This training will help reinforce your knowledge.</p><p><b>Rules:</b> Select a way to represent the counting. Half of the values will be preloaded, and you will complete the other half using the arrows on the side. When you finish, you can restart the training by clicking the \"Start again\" button.</p><p>Couting model: <input type=\"radio\" value=\"ha\" name=\"selModel\" /> <b><span id=\"firstMethod\"></span></b> <input type=\"radio\" value=\"indigenous\" name=\"selModel\" /> <b><span id=\"secondMethod\"></span></b> <input id=\"playButton\" type=\"button\" /></p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><table id=\"yupana0\" class=\"tawapukllay\"><tr><th colspan=\"4\">Translate the second line using arrows on side.</th><th>Increase</th><th>Decrease</th></tr> <tr id=\"tf1\"><td id=\"tc1f1\">&nbsp;</td> <td id=\"tc2f1\">&nbsp;</td> <td id=\"tc3f1\">&nbsp;</td> <td id=\"tc4f1\">&nbsp;</td><td id=\"tc5f1\" rowspan=\"3\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-caret-up upArrowWithFA\" name=\"traineeUp\"></i> </td><td id=\"tc6f1\" rowspan=\"3\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-caret-down downArrowWithFA\" name=\"traineeDown\"></i></td></tr> <tr id=\"tf2\"><td id=\"tc1f2\">&nbsp;</td> <td id=\"tc2f2\">&nbsp;</td> <td id=\"tc3f2\">&nbsp;</td> <td id=\"tc4f2\">&nbsp;</td></tr> <tr><td colspan=\"4\"><span id=\"gameMessage\"></span></td></tr> </table>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_game",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "<p><h3>Discovering America (<i>Abya Ayala</i>)</h3><b>Objective and rules:</b>Our objective is to translate the indigenous numerations that will appear, either on <i>Yupana</i> format or in the Mesoamerican format. With each value you translate, you will learn about an indigenous region in America (<i>Abya Ayala</i>). You can advance to the next mission by clicking on <i class=\"fa-solid fa-play\" style=\"color: Tomato;\"></i>. At the end, you will receive a medal (<i class=\"fa-solid fa-medal\" style=\"color:gold;\"></i>) for your work.</p><p><b>Note:</b> To read a number on the Yupana, we must look at all four squares. In contrast, Mesoamerican numbers are represented in a single square.</p><p><table id=\"yupana1\" class=\"tawapukllay\"><tr><th colspan=\"4\">Translate the first line and discover indigenous constructions.</th></tr> <tr id=\"tf1\"><td id=\"tc1f1\">&nbsp;</td> <td id=\"tc2f1\">&nbsp;</td> <td id=\"tc3f1\">&nbsp;</td> <td id=\"tc4f1\">&nbsp;</td></tr> <tr id=\"tf2\"><td id=\"tc1f2\">&nbsp;</div></td> <td id=\"tc2f2\">&nbsp;</td> <td id=\"tc3f2\">&nbsp;</td> <td id=\"tc4f2\">&nbsp;</td></tr> <tr id=\"tf3\"><td colspan=\"3\" id=\"tc1f3\"><span id=\"gameImage\"></span></td><td id=\"tc4f3\"><div id=\"descImage\"></div> <span style=\"font-size: 3em; color: Tomato;\"><i id=\"nextLevel\" class=\"fa-solid fa-play\"></i></span></td></tr> </table>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p class=\"desc\">We work with <i>Yupana</i> using the <i>\"Yupana Inka Tawa Pukllay\"</i> method, developed and published by Dhavit Prem (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('2d2ea4a5-506b-4dbf-aaa4-3a10a8fbbd9c'); return false;\">Prem, Dhavit</a>) of the Yupanki Association (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('a62b520a-f443-4d83-ab51-b99c9a46dab8'); return false;\">Prem, Dhavit, <htdate0></a>).<br />The use of Mesoamerican numbers is based on the work of Orlando Josué Casares Contreras, José M. Gamboa Cetina y Venus Sarahí Estrella Cabrera (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('ad11b3b2-8cdf-4d71-9cb7-2ac241850945'); return false;\">Casares Contreras, Orlando & Cetina, José & Cabrera, Venus Sarahí, <htdate1>, (ResearchGate)</a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('eca99877-c520-4569-a71c-0a5b3dd77dc4'); return false;\">Casares Contreras, Orlando & Cetina, José & Cabrera, Venus Sarahí, <htdate2>, (Revista)</a>). Additionally, we incorporate the work of Francisco Barriga Puente, and Ximena Catepillán (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('ceffba8a-43be-4de3-a5c8-27cdf81311b1'); return false;\">Puente, Francisco Barriga, <htdate3></a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('ced67eaf-7378-4589-9166-07f799969e3e'); return false;\">Catepillán, Ximena, <htdate4></a>).<br /> Finally, we utilize various counting methods inspired by the work of Francisco A. González Redondo <i>et al.</i> (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('a4f22e25-5839-407f-a1aa-634521d52b42'); return false;\">González Redondo, Francisco A., et al., <htdate5></a>).</p>",
